4.8.1.4.2. Device Models Sections & Details

  


Requirements

Overview: The Device Model is a Sales Item with a Category of "Device Model". Each Device record would have a Device Model selected on it.

  


Accessed via: 

  * The Device Models report (see the corresponding section of this proposal) 



  


Custom Sections and Fields (visible if Category = Device Model): 

  * Model Details section: 
    * Brand (required; drop list of Brand items)
    * Model (required; text field; duplicates are allowed to handle various versions of the same Model, i.e. "New", "Refurbished", etc.) 
    * Numeric Model (required; plain text field; used to track just the numeric portion of the Model for use in the Device Description; error on Save if duplicated: "This Numeric Model is already being used by another Model record. Change the info to make it unique."; if multiple Model records are to be set up for models in the same series, or new vs. refurbished, a suffix can be added to differentiate between them) 
    * Note in black text: "To be used with Device ID for Device Description." 
    * Printer (required; drop list of Yes, No; defaults to blank; used to specify if a Model (and therefore any Device the Model is used for) is a printer)
    * Print Type (visible and required if Printer = Yes; drop list of "Mono" and "Color"; defaults to blank; if "Mono", the Color-related fields on the Device record are non-editable) 
    * Manual Print Count Instructions (visible if Printer = Yes; memo; used for documenting instructions for manually collecting page counts; warning on Save if blank: "There are no notes in Manual Page Count Instructions for this Model.") 



  


  * Warranty Options section: 
    * Manufacturer's Standard Warranty (optional; warning on Save if blank: "Manufacturer's Standard Warranty is blank."; number with no decimals; used to track the number of months for the warranty; includes a "months" label after the field, like this: "[___] months")
    * Manufacturer's Warranty Details (optional; multi-line plain text field; used to document a brand's warranty phone number, etc.)
    * Available Extended Warranties (embedded spreadsheet with the following:)
      * Columns: 
        * Warranty Name (required; drop list of Names of active Warranty items) 
        * Terms (Months) (auto-set and read-only) 
        * Amount/Price (auto-set and read-only) 
        * View ("Link"; opens the corresponding Warranty item)
      * Automatically sorted by: Terms (Months) (highest number at the top) 
      * Buttons to add/remove rows: "+" / "-"
      * Show 6 rows without scrolling
    * New Warranty Item (link; opens a blank Warranty-type Sales Item record) 



  


  * Monthly Service Plan Options section (Think Ink offers various Monthly Plans with different benefits and prices): 
    * Available Monthly Service Plans (embedded spreadsheet with the following:) 
      * Columns:
        * Plan Name (required; drop list of Monthly Service Plan Names) 
        * Monthly Base Price (required; number field to 2 decimals) 
        * Prepay Discounted Price (required; number field to 2 decimals)
        * Included Black Pages (visible and required if Printer = Yes; number field with no decimals)
        * Black Overage $ (visible and required if Printer = Yes; number field to 2 decimals)
        * Included Color Pages (visible and required if Printer = Yes and if Print Type = Color; number field with no decimals)
        * Color Overage $ (visible and required if Printer = Yes and if Print Type = Color; number field to 2 decimals)
        * Total Devices on Plan (auto-set and read-only; total number of active Devices with this plan selected)
      * Automatically sorted by: N/A (retains order of entry)
      * Buttons to insert/append/remove rows: "Insert", "Append", "Delete"
      * Buttons to move rows up and down (up/down arrows) 
      * Show 6 rows without scrolling
      * Other Notes:
        * If details are changed here for a Monthly Service Plan, the changes will not be reflected on Devices that are currently using the Plan. 



  


  * Add-Ons Section (Think Ink offers some Add-Ons to Managed Devices such as additional services or items that are billed in addition to the plan's base charge) 
    * Included Add-Ons (embedded spreadsheet with the following:) 
      * Columns: 
        * Description (required; drop list of ____ Sales Items; defaults to blank)

  * Default Monthly Charge (required; number field with 2 decimals; defaults to blank)


  * Automatically sorted by: alphabetically

Other Notes for Device Model Sales Items: 

  * Models are to be set up by Think Ink, with help from CCI/CH as needed.
  * There should be Device Models set up by Think Ink for "Email Account" and "Hotspot", to allow for handling those Manged Devices on the Device record.
  * Default $ fields can be set to "0.00" if no charge is applicable.
